The President of the United States sends warm wishes to Nigeria as they inaugurate a new President. The US administration aims to strengthen ties between the two countries, focusing on economic growth, security, and human rights. The vibrant Nigerian Diaspora in the US has fostered deep people-to-people connections. Nigeria's success is seen as a global success, and elected leaders should demonstrate that democracy can meet the needs of the people. The US pledges to continue working closely with Nigeria as a friend and partner for a more peaceful and prosperous future.